<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                                Colonel <persName type="to">Marshall S. Carter</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-29">29 July
                                1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>32. I agree with objective of McCabe’s suggested delegation, your 95432
                            refers. Incidentally, if McCabe delegation can help in final settlement
                            of the yuan indebtedness, so much the better.</p>
                        <p>The seething economic-political-military situation in China might
                            conceivably interfere with definite accomplishment by the delegation,
                            hence all members must be steeled against possible disappointment.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>